SUMMARY:Moving Fast Without Breaking Things Using GitHub Code Quality
DESCRIPTION:Microsoft Reactor Toronto\nAI tools like GitHub Copilot are ac
 celerating development—but speed alone doesn’t guarantee sustainable c
 ode. Without clear signals and prioritization\, teams risk accumulating te
 chnical debt faster than they can understand it. This talk introduces GitH
 ub Code Quality\, a developer-first approach to maintaining reliability an
 d maintainability in AI-assisted codebases.\n\nYou’ll learn how Code Qua
 lity highlights the issues that matter most\, avoids noisy backlogs\, and 
 enables automated fixes—helping teams ship faster while staying in contr
 ol of long-term code health.\n\n📌 This session is a part of a series! [
 Learn more here](https://developer.microsoft.com/reactor/series/S-1625/?wt
 .mc_id=meetup_S-1625_webpage_reactor)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/microsoft-reactor-toronto/events/3132
 44028/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260206T233517Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260206T233517Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Microsoft Reactor Toronto
UID:event_313945922@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
