SUMMARY:OpenClawNet - Scaffolding + Gateway + Local Chat
DESCRIPTION:Microsoft Reactor Toronto\nIn this session we will build a ful
 ly connected .NET 10 solution that will be the core of OpenClawNet. We wil
 l wire up .NET Aspire for service orchestration\, build the Gateway API us
 ing Minimal APIs\, add real-time chat with SignalR\, create a Blazor web U
 I\, connect to Ollama for local AI inference\, and persist chat history wi
 th SQLite and EF Core.\n\nAt the end we will have a fully functional local
  chatbot in your browser. Send a message\, watch it stream back from your 
 local LLM\, and see it persist to the database. A solid foundation for eve
 rything that comes next.\n\n**Key Topics & Technologies:**\n\n* Solution a
 rchitecture and project organization\n* Aspire service orchestration and h
 ealth checks\n* ASP.NET Core Minimal APIs and endpoint design\n* SignalR f
 or real-time WebSocket communication\n* Blazor (Server-side rendering) for
  interactive UI\n* Ollama integration for local LLM inference\n* SQLite wi
 th EF Core for session persistence\n* Gateway routing and middleware\n\nPr
 e-requisites:\n\n* **Experience:** Intermediate C# and ASP.NET Core knowle
 dge (not a .NET 101)\n* **Environment:** .NET 10 SDK\, VS Code + GitHub Co
 pilot (or Visual Studio)\, Docker (for Ollama)\n* **Optional:** Azure subs
 cription (for Sessions 3–4\, but local development works fine throughout
 )\n* **Mindset:** Curiosity about AI agents\, willingness to follow along 
 live and ask questions
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/microsoft-reactor-toronto/events/3139
 45922/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260325T174738Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260325T174738Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
