SUMMARY:GitHub Copilot CLI Hands-On: First Steps\, Context\, and Conversat
 ions
DESCRIPTION:Microsoft Reactor Toronto\nChapters Covered: Overview\, 01 –
  First Steps\, 02 – Context and Conversations\n\n-----------------------
 ---------------------------------\n\nWhat is GitHub Copilot CLI and how ca
 n you get started using it?\n\nIn this first session you'll get answers to
  those questions and run your first Copilot CLI commands against a coding 
 project. From there you'll learn about the three interaction modes that ar
 e available: Interactive\, Plan\, and Programmatic. You'll then learn how 
 to give Copilot better context with the @ syntax\, work across files and d
 irectories\, and carry conversations forward across multiple turns and ses
 sions.\n\nWith the skills you learn in this session\, you'll be able to re
 view and summarize existing code with context across multiple files\, plan
  new projects\, and generate code and documentation.\n\nThis is the first 
 of four sessions that walk you through the [**GitHub Copilot CLI for Begin
 ners course**](https://github.com/github/copilot-cli-for-beginners).\n\nTh
 is session is a part of a series. Learn more [here](https://developer.micr
 osoft.com/reactor/series/S-1648/?wt.mc_id=meetup_S-1648_webpage_reactor)\n
 \nPre-requisites:\nComplete [**Chapter 00**](https://github.com/github/cop
 ilot-cli-for-beginners/blob/main/00-quick-start/README.md) of the course t
 o install GitHub Copilot CLI and sign in.\n\n-----------------------------
 ----------------------------\n\n[⏱🌎 This series is offered in two tim
 e zones for your convenience. Looking for our APAC sessions? Click here.](
 https://developer.microsoft.com/reactor/series/S-1651/?wt.mc_id=1reg_26896
 _webpage_reactor)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/microsoft-reactor-toronto/events/3138
 72447/
