SUMMARY:Azure Decoded: Vibe Coding on Azure Cosmos DB: Build an AI App
DESCRIPTION:Microsoft Reactor Toronto\nJoin us for a fast kickoff to Azure
  Cosmos DB\, then watch a live\, end-to-end build in Visual Studio Code wh
 ere we create a new Cosmos DB database and wire up an app using modern dev
 eloper workflows.\n\nWe'll demo agent-based vibe coding with the Azure Cos
 mos DB Agent Kit\, showing how it plugs into agent-compatible coding assis
 tants (including GitHub Copilot in VS Code) to apply Cosmos DB best practi
 ces as you design data models\, choose distribution strategies\, and tune 
 queries and indexing.\n\nWe’ll wrap with practical guidance on integrati
 ng Cosmos DB with other Azure services—skills that align directly to the
  Microsoft Certified: Azure Cosmos DB Developer Specialty (DP-420 certific
 ation).\n\n**What you’ll learn:**\n• What is and how to get started wi
 th Azure Cosmos DB\n• Setting up your Azure Cosmos DB AI Development Kit
  (VS Code\, GitHub Copilot Chat\, Cosmos DB Extension\, GitHub Copilot for
  Azure\, Azure MCP – 3 points suggested\n• Creating a CRUD application
  with natural language\n\n**Who should attend:**\nDevelopers building clou
 d-native applications who want to skill up on Azure Cosmos DB and learn mo
 dern\, agent-assisted workflows in their IDE—plus anyone planning to att
 end Cosmos DB Conf or pursue the DP-420 Azure Cosmos DB Developer Specialt
 y certification.\n\n***\n\n[Azure Cosmos DB Agent Kit for AI coding assist
 ants](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/cosmos-db/gen-ai/agent-kit/?wt.mc_
 id=meetup_26885_webpage_reactor)\n[Get started with Azure Cosmos DB for No
 SQL](https://learn.microsoft.com/training/paths/get-started-azure-cosmos-d
 b-sql-api/?wt.mc_id=meetup_26885_webpage_reactor)\n[Get started with AI-as
 sisted development](https://learn.microsoft.com/training/paths/accelerate-
 app-development-using-github-copilot/?wt.mc_id=meetup_26885_webpage_reacto
 r)\n[Get started with GitHub Copilot](https://learn.microsoft.com/training
 /modules/get-started-github-copilot/?wt.mc_id=meetup_26885_webpage_reactor
 )
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/microsoft-reactor-toronto/events/3137
 61508/
